WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'Balaby' is a Workbench game based on those games where you have
to move a ball from one point of a maze-like pathway to another.

  The idea is to move a ball towards the Exit, indicated by an
'E', in the least amount of moves. This is done by 'rotating' the
game board, either clockwise or counterclockwise, using the
'turning' arrows that are located on either side of the displayed
board, so the ball falls down, following the law of physics; I.E.:
From the upper part toward the lower part of the game board.

  What complicates the game a little, is that only a 4 by 4 spaces
part of the entire 8 by 8 size game board is visible at a time. If
the ball falls down towards the lower part of the visible area and
there are no horizontal bar to stop it, the game will display the
lower part of the board where the ball goes to... until it reaches
either the edge or a horizontal bar located under.

  As you complete a game board, Balaby displays a new board and
the game continues...

  Have fun!

